{
  "texts": [
    "This heightened perception of behavioral control prompts Gen Z consumers to consider the environmental impact of their purchase decisions and motivate them to choose green apparel.",
    "Therefore, the following hypotheses are proposed: H11: The scale of environmental accidents has a positive impact on subjective norms in Gen Z's green apparel purchase behavior.",
    "The scale of environmental accidents has a positive impact on the perception of behavioral control in Gen Z's green apparel purchase behavior.",
    "Environmental accidents may affect subjective norms as situational cues can influence attitudes and behaviors.",
    "The nature of the event's effects may alter an individual's context, intensifying their sense of social responsibility and moral obligation."
  ]
}